# PCG River Generation Graph
# Generates river systems with tributaries and water flow patterns

# Graph Structure:
# Input: World Bounds + Source Points
# -> Spline Sampler (River path)
# -> Copy Points (Create river width)
# -> Transform Points (Depth variation)
# -> Attribute Set (Flow data)
# -> Static Mesh Spawner (River bed rocks)
# -> Output: River geometry and flow data

# Key Nodes Configuration:
# 1. Spline Sampler
#    - Mode: Distance
#    - Distance Between Points: 100cm
#    - Interior Sample: True
#
# 2. Copy Points (River Width)
#    - Copy Mode: Offset
#    - Offset Distance: 400cm (river width)
#    - Number of Copies: 8
#
# 3. Transform Points (Depth)
#    - Z Offset: -100cm to -300cm (river depth)
#    - Add noise for natural variation
#
# 4. Attribute Set
#    - FlowRate: 0.5 to 2.0 based on position
#    - Depth: Calculated from transform
#    - Width: Distance from center
#    - Turbulence: Noise-based water movement
#
# 5. Static Mesh Spawner
#    - Mesh: River rocks and pebbles
#    - Density: 0.3 (sparse placement)
#    - Scale: 0.5 to 1.5 random

# Output provides:
# - River bed geometry
# - Water flow parameters
# - Rock placement data
# - Erosion influence zones